The essential oil was extracted by the method of distillation with water using a Clevenger. To this purpose, 10 g of the harvested seeds were completely crushed, poured into specific flasks, and were added with 120 mL of distilled water. The process of essential oil extraction at boiling water temperature was kept on for 4 h. Essential oil yield per unit area, which is a function of essential oil content and seed yield, was calculated by the following equation:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
