In this assay, 9 mL of Tris-HCI buffer (pH 8.2, 50 mM L−1) was poured into a test tube and it was incubated in a hot bath at 25 °C for 20 min. Then, 40 µL of pyrogal solution (45 mM L−1 of pyrogallol in 10 mM L−1 of hydrochloric acid) that was already incubated at 25 °C was injected into the top part of the test tube with a 1-µL syringe and was mixed with it. The mixture was incubated at 25 °C for 3 min, immediately after which it was added with 1 drop of ascorbic acid to stop the reaction. The absorbance of the mixture at 420 nm was recorded as A0 after 5 min. A0 shows the autooxidation rate of pyrogallol. Autooxidation rate A1 was estimated by the same procedure. The only difference was that the Tris buffer was added only with 50 µL of the extract. At the same time, a control blank of the reaction material was considered as A296. The radical scavenging percentage was calculated by the following equation:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
